234QString Value::toString() const
235{
236 if (type == KnownIdentifier) {
237 return QLatin1StringView(values[indexOfId[variant.toInt()]].name);
238 } else {
239 return variant.toString();
240 }
241}

328static bool operator<(const QString &name, const QCssKnownValue &prop)
329{
330 return QString::compare(s1: name, s2: QLatin1StringView(prop.name), cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) < 0;
331}
332
333static bool operator<(const QCssKnownValue &prop, const QString &name)
334{
335 return QString::compare(s1: QLatin1StringView(prop.name), s2: name, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) < 0;
336}
337
338static quint64 findKnownValue(const QString &name, const QCssKnownValue *start, int numValues)
339{
340 const QCssKnownValue *end = start + numValues - 1;
341 const QCssKnownValue *prop = std::lower_bound(start, end, name);
342 if ((prop == end) || (name < *prop))
343 return 0;
344 return prop->id;
345}

347static inline bool isInheritable(Property propertyId)
348{
349 switch (propertyId) {
350 case Font:
351 case FontKerning:
352 case FontFamily:
353 case FontSize:
354 case FontStyle:
355 case FontWeight:
356 case TextIndent:
357 case Whitespace:
358 case ListStyleType:
359 case ListStyle:
360 case TextAlignment:
361 case FontVariant:
362 case TextTransform:
363 case LineHeight:
364 case LetterSpacing:
365 case WordSpacing:
366 return true;
367 default:
368 break;
369 }
370 return false;
371}

379
380LengthData ValueExtractor::lengthValue(const Value& v)
381{
382 const QString str = v.variant.toString();
383 QStringView s(str);
384 LengthData data;
385 data.unit = LengthData::None;
386 if (s.endsWith(s: u"px", cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive))
387 data.unit = LengthData::Px;
388 else if (s.endsWith(s: u"ex", cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive))
389 data.unit = LengthData::Ex;
390 else if (s.endsWith(s: u"em", cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive))
391 data.unit = LengthData::Em;
392
393 if (data.unit != LengthData::None)
394 s.chop(n: 2);
395
396 data.number = s.toDouble();
397 return data;
398}
399
400static int lengthValueFromData(const LengthData& data, const QFont& f)
401{
402 const int scale = (data.unit == LengthData::Ex ? QFontMetrics(f).xHeight()
403 : data.unit == LengthData::Em ? QFontMetrics(f).height() : 1);
404 // raised lower limit due to the implementation of qRound()
405 return qRound(d: qBound(min: double(INT_MIN) + 0.1, val: scale * data.number, max: double(INT_MAX)));
406}
407
408int ValueExtractor::lengthValue(const Declaration &decl)
409{
410 if (decl.d->parsed.isValid())
411 return lengthValueFromData(data: qvariant_cast<LengthData>(v: decl.d->parsed), f);
412 if (decl.d->values.size() < 1)
413 return 0;
414 LengthData data = lengthValue(v: decl.d->values.at(i: 0));
415 decl.d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<LengthData>(value: data);
416 return lengthValueFromData(data,f);
417}
418
419void ValueExtractor::lengthValues(const Declaration &decl, int *m)
420{
421 if (decl.d->parsed.isValid()) {
422 QList<QVariant> v = decl.d->parsed.toList();
423 Q_ASSERT(v.size() == 4);
424 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
425 m[i] = lengthValueFromData(data: qvariant_cast<LengthData>(v: v.at(i)), f);
426 return;
427 }
428
429 LengthData datas[4];
430 int i;
431 for (i = 0; i < qMin(a: decl.d->values.size(), b: 4); i++)
432 datas[i] = lengthValue(v: decl.d->values[i]);
433
434 if (i == 0) {
435 LengthData zero = {.number: 0.0, .unit: LengthData::None};
436 datas[0] = datas[1] = datas[2] = datas[3] = zero;
437 } else if (i == 1) {
438 datas[3] = datas[2] = datas[1] = datas[0];
439 } else if (i == 2) {
440 datas[2] = datas[0];
441 datas[3] = datas[1];
442 } else if (i == 3) {
443 datas[3] = datas[1];
444 }
445
446 QList<QVariant> v;
447 v.reserve(size: 4);
448 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
449 v += QVariant::fromValue<LengthData>(value: datas[i]);
450 m[i] = lengthValueFromData(data: datas[i], f);
451 }
452 decl.d->parsed = v;
453}
454
455bool ValueExtractor::extractGeometry(int *w, int *h, int *minw, int *minh, int *maxw, int *maxh)
456{
457 extractFont();
458 bool hit = false;
459 for (int i = 0; i < declarations.size(); i++) {
460 const Declaration &decl = declarations.at(i);
461 switch (decl.d->propertyId) {
462 case Width: *w = lengthValue(decl); break;
463 case Height: *h = lengthValue(decl); break;
464 case MinimumWidth: *minw = lengthValue(decl); break;
465 case MinimumHeight: *minh = lengthValue(decl); break;
466 case MaximumWidth: *maxw = lengthValue(decl); break;
467 case MaximumHeight: *maxh = lengthValue(decl); break;
468 default: continue;
469 }
470 hit = true;
471 }
472
473 return hit;
474}
475
476bool ValueExtractor::extractPosition(int *left, int *top, int *right, int *bottom, QCss::Origin *origin,
477 Qt::Alignment *position, QCss::PositionMode *mode, Qt::Alignment *textAlignment)
478{
479 extractFont();
480 bool hit = false;
481 for (int i = 0; i < declarations.size(); i++) {
482 const Declaration &decl = declarations.at(i);
483 switch (decl.d->propertyId) {
484 case Left: *left = lengthValue(decl); break;
485 case Top: *top = lengthValue(decl); break;
486 case Right: *right = lengthValue(decl); break;
487 case Bottom: *bottom = lengthValue(decl); break;

495 }

540{
541 if (decl.d->parsed.isValid()) {
542 QList<QVariant> v = decl.d->parsed.toList();
543 return QSize(lengthValueFromData(data: qvariant_cast<LengthData>(v: v.at(i: 0)), f),
544 lengthValueFromData(data: qvariant_cast<LengthData>(v: v.at(i: 1)), f));
545 }
546
547 LengthData x[2] = { {.number: 0, .unit: LengthData::None }, {.number: 0, .unit: LengthData::None} };
548 if (decl.d->values.size() > 0)

550 if (decl.d->values.size() > 1)

552 else
553 x[1] = x[0];
554 QList<QVariant> v;
555 v << QVariant::fromValue<LengthData>(value: x[0]) << QVariant::fromValue<LengthData>(value: x[1]);
556 decl.d->parsed = v;
557 return QSize(lengthValueFromData(data: x[0], f), lengthValueFromData(data: x[1], f));

660static Qt::Alignment parseAlignment(const QCss::Value *values, int count)
661{
662 Qt::Alignment a[2] = { { }, { } };
663 for (int i = 0; i < qMin(a: 2, b: count); i++) {
664 if (values[i].type != Value::KnownIdentifier)
665 break;
666 switch (values[i].variant.toInt()) {
667 case Value_Left: a[i] = Qt::AlignLeft; break;
668 case Value_Right: a[i] = Qt::AlignRight; break;
669 case Value_Top: a[i] = Qt::AlignTop; break;
670 case Value_Bottom: a[i] = Qt::AlignBottom; break;
671 case Value_Center: a[i] = Qt::AlignCenter; break;
672 default: break;
673 }
674 }
675
676 if (a[0] == Qt::AlignCenter && a[1] != 0 && a[1] != Qt::AlignCenter)
677 a[0] = (a[1] == Qt::AlignLeft || a[1] == Qt::AlignRight) ? Qt::AlignVCenter : Qt::AlignHCenter;
678 if ((a[1] == 0 || a[1] == Qt::AlignCenter) && a[0] != Qt::AlignCenter)
679 a[1] = (a[0] == Qt::AlignLeft || a[0] == Qt::AlignRight) ? Qt::AlignVCenter : Qt::AlignHCenter;
680 return a[0] | a[1];
681}
682
683static ColorData parseColorValue(QCss::Value v)
684{
685 if (v.type == Value::Identifier || v.type == Value::String) {
686 v.variant.convert(type: QMetaType::fromType<QColor>());
687 v.type = Value::Color;
688 }
689
690 if (v.type == Value::Color)
691 return qvariant_cast<QColor>(v: v.variant);
692
693 if (v.type == Value::KnownIdentifier && v.variant.toInt() == Value_Transparent)
694 return QColor(Qt::transparent);
695
696 if (v.type != Value::Function)
697 return ColorData();
698
699 QStringList lst = v.variant.toStringList();
700 if (lst.size() != 2)
701 return ColorData();
702
703 const QString &identifier = lst.at(i: 0);
704 if ((identifier.compare(other: "palette"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)) == 0) {
705 int role = findKnownValue(name: lst.at(i: 1).trimmed(), start: values, numValues: NumKnownValues);
706 if (role >= Value_FirstColorRole && role <= Value_LastColorRole)
707 return (QPalette::ColorRole)(role-Value_FirstColorRole);
708
709 return ColorData();
710 }
711
712 const bool rgb = identifier.startsWith(s: "rgb"_L1);
713 const bool hsv = !rgb && identifier.startsWith(s: "hsv"_L1);
714 const bool hsl = !rgb && !hsv && identifier.startsWith(s: "hsl"_L1);
715
716 if (!rgb && !hsv && !hsl)
717 return ColorData();
718
719 const bool hasAlpha = identifier.size() == 4 && identifier.at(i: 3) == u'a';
720 if (identifier.size() > 3 && !hasAlpha)
721 return ColorData();
722
723 Parser p(lst.at(i: 1));
724 if (!p.testExpr())
725 return ColorData();
726
727 QList<QCss::Value> colorDigits;
728 if (!p.parseExpr(values: &colorDigits))
729 return ColorData();
730 const int tokenCount = colorDigits.size();
731
732 for (int i = 0; i < qMin(a: tokenCount, b: 7); i += 2) {
733 if (colorDigits.at(i).type == Value::Percentage) {
734 const qreal maxRange = (rgb || i != 0) ? 255. : 359.;
735 colorDigits[i].variant = colorDigits.at(i).variant.toReal() * (maxRange / 100.);
736 colorDigits[i].type = Value::Number;
737 } else if (colorDigits.at(i).type != Value::Number) {
738 return ColorData();
739 }
740 }
741
742
743 if (tokenCount < 5)
744 return ColorData();
745
746 if (hasAlpha && tokenCount != 7) {
747 qWarning(msg: "QCssParser::parseColorValue: Specified color with alpha value but no alpha given: '%s'", qPrintable(lst.join(u' ')));
748 return ColorData();
749 }
750 if (!hasAlpha && tokenCount != 5) {
751 qWarning(msg: "QCssParser::parseColorValue: Specified color without alpha value but alpha given: '%s'", qPrintable(lst.join(u' ')));
752 return ColorData();
753 }
754
755 int v1 = colorDigits.at(i: 0).variant.toInt();
756 int v2 = colorDigits.at(i: 2).variant.toInt();
757 int v3 = colorDigits.at(i: 4).variant.toInt();
758 int alpha = 255;
759 if (tokenCount == 7) {
760 int alphaValue = colorDigits.at(i: 6).variant.toInt();
761 if (alphaValue <= 1)
762 alpha = colorDigits.at(i: 6).variant.toReal() * 255.;
763 else
764 alpha = alphaValue;
765 }
766
767 if (rgb)
768 return QColor::fromRgb(r: v1, g: v2, b: v3, a: alpha);
769 if (hsv)
770 return QColor::fromHsv(h: v1, s: v2, v: v3, a: alpha);
771 return QColor::fromHsl(h: v1, s: v2, l: v3, a: alpha);
772}
773
774static QColor colorFromData(const ColorData& c, const QPalette &pal)
775{
776 if (c.type == ColorData::Color) {
777 return c.color;
778 } else if (c.type == ColorData::Role) {
779 return pal.color(cr: c.role);
780 }
781 return QColor();
782}

784static BrushData parseBrushValue(const QCss::Value &v, const QPalette &pal)
785{
786 ColorData c = parseColorValue(v);
787 if (c.type == ColorData::Color) {
788 return QBrush(c.color);
789 } else if (c.type == ColorData::Role) {
790 return c.role;
791 }
792
793 if (v.type != Value::Function)
794 return BrushData();
795
796 QStringList lst = v.variant.toStringList();
797 if (lst.size() != 2)
798 return BrushData();
799
800 QStringList gradFuncs;
801 gradFuncs << "qlineargradient"_L1 << "qradialgradient"_L1 << "qconicalgradient"_L1 << "qgradient"_L1;
802 int gradType = -1;
803
804 if ((gradType = gradFuncs.indexOf(str: lst.at(i: 0).toLower())) == -1)
805 return BrushData();
806
807 QHash<QString, qreal> vars;
808 QList<QGradientStop> stops;
809
810 int spread = -1;
811 QStringList spreads;
812 spreads << "pad"_L1 << "reflect"_L1 << "repeat"_L1;
813
814 bool dependsOnThePalette = false;
815 Parser parser(lst.at(i: 1));
816 while (parser.hasNext()) {
817 parser.skipSpace();
818 if (!parser.test(t: IDENT))
819 return BrushData();
820 QString attr = parser.lexem();
821 parser.skipSpace();
822 if (!parser.test(t: COLON))
823 return BrushData();
824 parser.skipSpace();
825 if (attr.compare(other: "stop"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
826 QCss::Value stop, color;
827 parser.next();
828 if (!parser.parseTerm(value: &stop)) return BrushData();
829 parser.skipSpace();
830 parser.next();
831 if (!parser.parseTerm(value: &color)) return BrushData();
832 ColorData cd = parseColorValue(v: color);
833 if (cd.type == ColorData::Role)
834 dependsOnThePalette = true;
835 stops.append(t: QGradientStop(stop.variant.toReal(), colorFromData(c: cd, pal)));
836 } else {
837 parser.next();
838 QCss::Value value;
839 (void)parser.parseTerm(value: &value);
840 if (attr.compare(other: "spread"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
841 spread = spreads.indexOf(str: value.variant.toString());
842 } else {
843 vars[attr] = value.variant.toReal();
844 }
845 }
846 parser.skipSpace();
847 (void)parser.test(t: COMMA);
848 }
849
850 if (gradType == 0) {
851 QLinearGradient lg(vars.value(key: "x1"_L1), vars.value(key: "y1"_L1),
852 vars.value(key: "x2"_L1), vars.value(key: "y2"_L1));
853 lg.setCoordinateMode(QGradient::ObjectBoundingMode);
854 lg.setStops(stops);
855 if (spread != -1)
856 lg.setSpread(QGradient::Spread(spread));
857 BrushData bd = QBrush(lg);
858 if (dependsOnThePalette)
859 bd.type = BrushData::DependsOnThePalette;
860 return bd;
861 }
862
863 if (gradType == 1) {
864 QRadialGradient rg(vars.value(key: "cx"_L1), vars.value(key: "cy"_L1),
865 vars.value(key: "radius"_L1), vars.value(key: "fx"_L1),
866 vars.value(key: "fy"_L1));
867 rg.setCoordinateMode(QGradient::ObjectBoundingMode);
868 rg.setStops(stops);
869 if (spread != -1)
870 rg.setSpread(QGradient::Spread(spread));
871 BrushData bd = QBrush(rg);
872 if (dependsOnThePalette)
873 bd.type = BrushData::DependsOnThePalette;
874 return bd;
875 }
876
877 if (gradType == 2) {
878 QConicalGradient cg(vars.value(key: "cx"_L1), vars.value(key: "cy"_L1), vars.value(key: "angle"_L1));
879 cg.setCoordinateMode(QGradient::ObjectBoundingMode);
880 cg.setStops(stops);
881 if (spread != -1)
882 cg.setSpread(QGradient::Spread(spread));
883 BrushData bd = QBrush(cg);
884 if (dependsOnThePalette)
885 bd.type = BrushData::DependsOnThePalette;
886 return bd;
887 }
888
889 return BrushData();
890}

893{
894 if (c.type == BrushData::Role) {
895 return pal.color(cr: c.role);
896 } else {
897 return c.brush;

937void ValueExtractor::borderValue(const Declaration &decl, int *width, QCss::BorderStyle *style, QBrush *color)
938{
939 if (decl.d->parsed.isValid()) {
940 BorderData data = qvariant_cast<BorderData>(v: decl.d->parsed);
941 *width = lengthValueFromData(data: data.width, f);
942 *style = data.style;
943 *color = data.color.type != BrushData::Invalid ? brushFromData(c: data.color, pal) : QBrush(QColor());
944 return;
945 }
946
947 *width = 0;
948 *style = BorderStyle_None;
949 *color = QColor();
950
951 if (decl.d->values.isEmpty())
952 return;
953
954 BorderData data;
955 data.width.number = 0;
956 data.width.unit = LengthData::None;
957 data.style = BorderStyle_None;
958
959 int i = 0;
960 if (decl.d->values.at(i).type == Value::Length || decl.d->values.at(i).type == Value::Number) {
961 data.width = lengthValue(v: decl.d->values.at(i));
962 *width = lengthValueFromData(data: data.width, f);
963 if (++i >= decl.d->values.size()) {
964 decl.d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<BorderData>(value: data);
965 return;
966 }
967 }
968
969 data.style = parseStyleValue(v: decl.d->values.at(i));
970 if (data.style != BorderStyle_Unknown) {
971 *style = data.style;
972 if (++i >= decl.d->values.size()) {
973 decl.d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<BorderData>(value: data);
974 return;
975 }
976 } else {
977 data.style = BorderStyle_None;
978 }
979
980 data.color = parseBrushValue(v: decl.d->values.at(i), pal);
981 *color = brushFromData(c: data.color, pal);
982 if (data.color.type != BrushData::DependsOnThePalette)
983 decl.d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<BorderData>(value: data);
984}

986static void parseShorthandBackgroundProperty(const QList<QCss::Value> &values, BrushData *brush, QString *image, Repeat *repeat, Qt::Alignment *alignment, const QPalette &pal)
987{
988 *brush = BrushData();
989 *image = QString();
990 *repeat = Repeat_XY;
991 *alignment = Qt::AlignTop | Qt::AlignLeft;
992
993 for (int i = 0; i < values.size(); ++i) {
994 const QCss::Value &v = values.at(i);
995 if (v.type == Value::Uri) {
996 *image = v.variant.toString();
997 continue;
998 } else if (v.type == Value::KnownIdentifier && v.variant.toInt() == Value_None) {
999 *image = QString();
1000 continue;
1001 } else if (v.type == Value::KnownIdentifier && v.variant.toInt() == Value_Transparent) {
1002 *brush = QBrush(Qt::transparent);
1003 }
1004
1005 Repeat repeatAttempt = static_cast<Repeat>(findKnownValue(name: v.variant.toString(),
1006 start: repeats, numValues: NumKnownRepeats));
1007 if (repeatAttempt != Repeat_Unknown) {
1008 *repeat = repeatAttempt;
1009 continue;
1010 }
1011
1012 if (v.type == Value::KnownIdentifier) {
1013 const int start = i;
1014 int count = 1;
1015 if (i < values.size() - 1
1016 && values.at(i: i + 1).type == Value::KnownIdentifier) {
1017 ++i;
1018 ++count;
1019 }
1020 Qt::Alignment a = parseAlignment(values: values.constData() + start, count);
1021 if (int(a) != 0) {
1022 *alignment = a;
1023 continue;
1024 }
1025 i -= count - 1;
1026 }
1027
1028 *brush = parseBrushValue(v, pal);
1029 }
1030}
1031
1032bool ValueExtractor::extractBackground(QBrush *brush, QString *image, Repeat *repeat,
1033 Qt::Alignment *alignment, Origin *origin, Attachment *attachment,
1034 Origin *clip)
1035{
1036 bool hit = false;
1037 for (int i = 0; i < declarations.size(); ++i) {
1038 const Declaration &decl = declarations.at(i);
1039 if (decl.d->values.isEmpty())
1040 continue;
1041 const QCss::Value &val = decl.d->values.at(i: 0);
1042 switch (decl.d->propertyId) {
1043 case BackgroundColor:
1044 *brush = decl.brushValue();
1045 break;
1046 case BackgroundImage:
1047 if (val.type == Value::Uri)
1048 *image = val.variant.toString();
1049 break;
1050 case BackgroundRepeat:
1051 if (decl.d->parsed.isValid()) {
1052 *repeat = static_cast<Repeat>(decl.d->parsed.toInt());
1053 } else {
1054 *repeat = static_cast<Repeat>(findKnownValue(name: val.variant.toString(),
1055 start: repeats, numValues: NumKnownRepeats));
1056 decl.d->parsed = *repeat;
1057 }
1058 break;
1059 case BackgroundPosition:
1060 *alignment = decl.alignmentValue();
1061 break;
1062 case BackgroundOrigin:
1063 *origin = decl.originValue();
1064 break;
1065 case BackgroundClip:
1066 *clip = decl.originValue();
1067 break;
1068 case Background:
1069 if (decl.d->parsed.isValid()) {
1070 BackgroundData data = qvariant_cast<BackgroundData>(v: decl.d->parsed);
1071 *brush = brushFromData(c: data.brush, pal);
1072 *image = data.image;
1073 *repeat = data.repeat;
1074 *alignment = data.alignment;
1075 } else {
1076 BrushData brushData;
1077 parseShorthandBackgroundProperty(values: decl.d->values, brush: &brushData, image, repeat, alignment, pal);
1078 *brush = brushFromData(c: brushData, pal);
1079 if (brushData.type != BrushData::DependsOnThePalette) {
1080 BackgroundData data = { .brush: brushData, .image: *image, .repeat: *repeat, .alignment: *alignment };
1081 decl.d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<BackgroundData>(value: data);
1082 }
1083 }
1084 break;
1085 case BackgroundAttachment:
1086 *attachment = decl.attachmentValue();
1087 break;
1088 default: continue;
1089 }
1090 hit = true;
1091 }
1092 return hit;
1093}

1095static bool setFontSizeFromValue(QCss::Value value, QFont *font, int *fontSizeAdjustment)
1096{
1097 if (value.type == Value::KnownIdentifier) {
1098 bool valid = true;
1099 switch (value.variant.toInt()) {
1100 case Value_Small: *fontSizeAdjustment = -1; break;
1101 case Value_Medium: *fontSizeAdjustment = 0; break;
1102 case Value_Large: *fontSizeAdjustment = 1; break;
1103 case Value_XLarge: *fontSizeAdjustment = 2; break;
1104 case Value_XXLarge: *fontSizeAdjustment = 3; break;
1105 default: valid = false; break;
1106 }
1107 return valid;
1108 }
1109 if (value.type != Value::Length)
1110 return false;
1111
1112 bool valid = false;
1113 QString s = value.variant.toString();
1114 if (s.endsWith(s: "pt"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)) {
1115 s.chop(n: 2);
1116 value.variant = s;
1117 if (value.variant.convert(type: QMetaType::fromType<qreal>())) {
1118 font->setPointSizeF(qBound(min: qreal(0), val: value.variant.toReal(), max: qreal(1 << 24) - 1));
1119 valid = true;
1120 }
1121 } else if (s.endsWith(s: "px"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)) {
1122 s.chop(n: 2);
1123 value.variant = s;
1124 if (value.variant.convert(type: QMetaType::fromType<int>())) {
1125 font->setPixelSize(qBound(min: 0, val: value.variant.toInt(), max: (1 << 24) - 1));
1126 valid = true;
1127 }
1128 }
1129 return valid;
1130}

1158static bool setFontWeightFromValue(const QCss::Value &value, QFont *font)
1159{

1175/** \internal
1176 * parse the font family from the values (starting from index \a start)
1177 * and set it the \a font
1178 * The function returns \c true if a family was extracted.
1179 */
1180static bool setFontFamilyFromValues(const QList<QCss::Value> &values, QFont *font, int start = 0)
1181{
1182 QString family;
1183 QStringList families;
1184 bool shouldAddSpace = false;
1185 for (int i = start; i < values.size(); ++i) {
1186 const QCss::Value &v = values.at(i);
1187 if (v.type == Value::TermOperatorComma) {
1188 families << family;
1189 family.clear();
1190 shouldAddSpace = false;
1191 continue;
1192 }
1193 const QString str = v.variant.toString();
1194 if (str.isEmpty())
1195 break;
1196 if (shouldAddSpace)
1197 family += u' ';
1198 family += str;
1199 shouldAddSpace = true;
1200 }
1201 if (!family.isEmpty())
1202 families << family;
1203 if (families.isEmpty())
1204 return false;
1205 font->setFamilies(families);
1206 return true;
1207}

1259static void parseShorthandFontProperty(const QList<QCss::Value> &values, QFont *font, int *fontSizeAdjustment)
1260{
1261 font->setStyle(QFont::StyleNormal);
1262 font->setWeight(QFont::Normal);
1263 *fontSizeAdjustment = -255;
1264
1265 int i = 0;
1266 while (i < values.size()) {
1267 if (setFontStyleFromValue(value: values.at(i), font)
1268 || setFontWeightFromValue(value: values.at(i), font))
1269 ++i;
1270 else
1271 break;
1272 }
1273
1274 if (i < values.size()) {
1275 setFontSizeFromValue(value: values.at(i), font, fontSizeAdjustment);
1276 ++i;
1277 }
1278
1279 if (i < values.size()) {
1280 setFontFamilyFromValues(values, font, start: i);
1281 }
1282}

1307bool ValueExtractor::extractFont(QFont *font, int *fontSizeAdjustment)
1308{
1309 if (fontExtracted) {
1310 *font = f;
1311 *fontSizeAdjustment = adjustment;
1312 return fontExtracted == 1;
1313 }
1314
1315 bool hit = false;
1316 for (int i = 0; i < declarations.size(); ++i) {
1317 const Declaration &decl = declarations.at(i);
1318 if (decl.d->values.isEmpty())
1319 continue;
1320 const QCss::Value &val = decl.d->values.at(i: 0);
1321 switch (decl.d->propertyId) {
1322 case FontSize: setFontSizeFromValue(value: val, font, fontSizeAdjustment); break;
1323 case FontStyle: setFontStyleFromValue(value: val, font); break;
1324 case FontWeight: setFontWeightFromValue(value: val, font); break;
1325 case FontFamily: setFontFamilyFromValues(values: decl.d->values, font); break;
1326 case FontKerning: setFontKerningFromValue(value: val, font); break;
1327 case TextDecoration: setTextDecorationFromValues(values: decl.d->values, font); break;
1328 case Font: parseShorthandFontProperty(values: decl.d->values, font, fontSizeAdjustment); break;
1329 case FontVariant: setFontVariantFromValue(value: val, font); break;
1330 case TextTransform: setTextTransformFromValue(value: val, font); break;
1331 case LetterSpacing: setLetterSpacingFromValue(value: val, font); break;
1332 case WordSpacing: setWordSpacingFromValue(value: val, font); break;
1333 default: continue;
1334 }
1335 hit = true;
1336 }
1337
1338 f = *font;
1339 adjustment = *fontSizeAdjustment;
1340 fontExtracted = hit ? 1 : 2;
1341 return hit;
1342}

1344bool ValueExtractor::extractPalette(QBrush *fg, QBrush *sfg, QBrush *sbg, QBrush *abg, QBrush *pfg)
1345{
1346 bool hit = false;
1347 for (int i = 0; i < declarations.size(); ++i) {
1348 const Declaration &decl = declarations.at(i);
1349 switch (decl.d->propertyId) {
1350 case Color: *fg = decl.brushValue(pal); break;
1351 case QtSelectionForeground: *sfg = decl.brushValue(pal); break;
1352 case QtSelectionBackground: *sbg = decl.brushValue(pal); break;
1353 case QtAlternateBackground: *abg = decl.brushValue(pal); break;
1354 case QtPlaceHolderTextColor: *pfg = decl.brushValue(pal); break;
1355 default: continue;
1356 }
1357 hit = true;
1358 }
1359 return hit;
1360}

1370bool ValueExtractor::extractImage(QIcon *icon, Qt::Alignment *a, QSize *size)
1371{
1372 bool hit = false;
1373 for (int i = 0; i < declarations.size(); ++i) {
1374 const Declaration &decl = declarations.at(i);
1375 switch (decl.d->propertyId) {
1376 case QtImage:
1377 *icon = decl.iconValue();
1378 if (decl.d->values.size() > 0 && decl.d->values.at(i: 0).type == Value::Uri) {
1379 // try to pull just the size from the image...
1380 QImageReader imageReader(decl.d->values.at(i: 0).variant.toString());
1381 if ((*size = imageReader.size()).isNull()) {
1382 // but we'll have to load the whole image if the
1383 // format doesn't support just reading the size
1384 *size = imageReader.read().size();
1385 }
1386 }
1387 break;
1388 case QtImageAlignment: *a = decl.alignmentValue(); break;
1389 default: continue;
1390 }
1391 hit = true;
1392 }
1393 return hit;
1394}
1395
1396bool ValueExtractor::extractIcon(QIcon *icon, QSize *size)
1397{
1398 // Find last declaration that specifies an icon
1399 const auto declaration = std::find_if(
1400 first: declarations.rbegin(), last: declarations.rend(),
1401 pred: [](const Declaration &decl) { return decl.d->propertyId == QtIcon; });
1402 if (declaration == declarations.rend())
1403 return false;
1404
1405 *icon = declaration->iconValue();
1406
1407 // If the value contains a URI, try to get the size of the icon
1408 if (declaration->d->values.isEmpty())
1409 return true;
1410
1411 const auto &propertyValue = declaration->d->values.constFirst();
1412 if (propertyValue.type != Value::Uri)
1413 return true;
1414
1415 // First try to read just the size from the image without loading it
1416 const QString url(propertyValue.variant.toString());
1417 QImageReader imageReader(url);
1418 *size = imageReader.size();
1419 if (!size->isNull())
1420 return true;
1421
1422 // Get the size by loading the image instead
1423 *size = imageReader.read().size();
1424 return true;
1425}

1429QColor Declaration::colorValue(const QPalette &pal) const
1430{
1431 if (d->values.size() != 1)
1432 return QColor();
1433
1434 if (d->parsed.isValid()) {
1435 switch (d->parsed.typeId()) {
1436 case qMetaTypeId<QColor>():
1437 return qvariant_cast<QColor>(v: d->parsed);
1438 case qMetaTypeId<int>():
1439 return pal.color(cr: (QPalette::ColorRole)(d->parsed.toInt()));
1440 case qMetaTypeId<QList<QVariant>>():
1441 if (d->parsed.toList().size() == 1) {
1442 auto parsedList = d->parsed.toList();
1443 const auto &value = parsedList.at(i: 0);
1444 return qvariant_cast<QColor>(v: value);
1445 }
1446 break;
1447 }
1448 }
1449
1450 ColorData color = parseColorValue(v: d->values.at(i: 0));
1451 if (color.type == ColorData::Role) {
1452 d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<int>(value: color.role);
1453 return pal.color(cr: (QPalette::ColorRole)(color.role));
1454 } else {
1455 d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<QColor>(value: color.color);
1456 return color.color;
1457 }
1458}

1460QBrush Declaration::brushValue(const QPalette &pal) const
1461{
1462 if (d->values.size() != 1)
1463 return QBrush();
1464
1465 if (d->parsed.isValid()) {
1466 if (d->parsed.userType() == QMetaType::QBrush)
1467 return qvariant_cast<QBrush>(v: d->parsed);
1468 if (d->parsed.userType() == QMetaType::Int)
1469 return pal.color(cr: (QPalette::ColorRole)(d->parsed.toInt()));
1470 }
1471
1472 BrushData data = parseBrushValue(v: d->values.at(i: 0), pal);
1473
1474 if (data.type == BrushData::Role) {
1475 d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<int>(value: data.role);
1476 return pal.color(cr: (QPalette::ColorRole)(data.role));
1477 } else {
1478 if (data.type != BrushData::DependsOnThePalette)
1479 d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<QBrush>(value: data.brush);
1480 return data.brush;
1481 }
1482}
1483
1484void Declaration::brushValues(QBrush *c, const QPalette &pal) const
1485{
1486 int needParse = 0x1f; // bits 0..3 say if we should parse the corresponding value.
1487 // the bit 4 say we need to update d->parsed
1488 int i = 0;
1489 if (d->parsed.isValid()) {
1490 needParse = 0;
1491 Q_ASSERT(d->parsed.metaType() == QMetaType::fromType<QList<QVariant>>());
1492 QList<QVariant> v = d->parsed.toList();
1493 for (i = 0; i < qMin(a: v.size(), b: 4); i++) {
1494 if (v.at(i).userType() == QMetaType::QBrush) {
1495 c[i] = qvariant_cast<QBrush>(v: v.at(i));
1496 } else if (v.at(i).userType() == QMetaType::Int) {
1497 c[i] = pal.color(cr: (QPalette::ColorRole)(v.at(i).toInt()));
1498 } else {
1499 needParse |= (1<<i);
1500 }
1501 }
1502 }
1503 if (needParse != 0) {
1504 QList<QVariant> v;
1505 for (i = 0; i < qMin(a: d->values.size(), b: 4); i++) {
1506 if (!(needParse & (1<<i)))
1507 continue;
1508 BrushData data = parseBrushValue(v: d->values.at(i), pal);
1509 if (data.type == BrushData::Role) {
1510 v += QVariant::fromValue<int>(value: data.role);
1511 c[i] = pal.color(cr: (QPalette::ColorRole)(data.role));
1512 } else {
1513 if (data.type != BrushData::DependsOnThePalette) {
1514 v += QVariant::fromValue<QBrush>(value: data.brush);
1515 } else {
1516 v += QVariant();
1517 }
1518 c[i] = data.brush;
1519 }
1520 }
1521 if (needParse & 0x10)
1522 d->parsed = v;
1523 }
1524 if (i == 0) c[0] = c[1] = c[2] = c[3] = QBrush();
1525 else if (i == 1) c[3] = c[2] = c[1] = c[0];
1526 else if (i == 2) c[2] = c[0], c[3] = c[1];
1527 else if (i == 3) c[3] = c[1];
1528}

1577
1578QSize Declaration::sizeValue() const
1579{
1580 if (d->parsed.isValid())
1581 return qvariant_cast<QSize>(v: d->parsed);
1582
1583 int x[2] = { 0, 0 };
1584 const int count = d->values.size();
1585 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
1586 if (i > 1) {
1587 qWarning(msg: "QCssParser::sizeValue: Too many values provided");
1588 break;
1589 }
1590 const auto &value = d->values.at(i);
1591 const QString valueString = value.variant.toString();
1592 if (valueString.endsWith(s: u"pt", cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)) {
1593 intValueHelper(v: value, i: &x[i], unit: "pt");
1594 // according to https://www.w3.org/TR/css3-values/#absolute-lengths
1595 // 1pt = 1/72th of 1 inch, and 1px = 1/96th of 1 inch
1596 x[i] = (x[i] * 72) / 96;
1597 } else {
1598 // by default we use 'px'
1599 intValueHelper(v: value, i: &x[i], unit: "px");
1600 }
1601 }
1602 if (count == 1)
1603 x[1] = x[0];
1604 QSize size(x[0], x[1]);
1605 d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<QSize>(value: size);
1606 return size;
1607}

1880quint64 Selector::pseudoClass(quint64 *negated) const
1881{

1884 return PseudoClass_Unspecified;

1900void StyleSheet::buildIndexes(Qt::CaseSensitivity nameCaseSensitivity)
1901{
1902 QList<StyleRule> universals;
1903 for (int i = 0; i < styleRules.size(); ++i) {
1904 const StyleRule &rule = styleRules.at(i);
1905 QList<Selector> universalsSelectors;
1906 for (int j = 0; j < rule.selectors.size(); ++j) {
1907 const Selector& selector = rule.selectors.at(i: j);
1908
1909 if (selector.basicSelectors.isEmpty())
1910 continue;
1911
1912 if (selector.basicSelectors.at(i: 0).relationToNext == BasicSelector::NoRelation) {
1913 if (selector.basicSelectors.size() != 1)
1914 continue;
1915 } else if (selector.basicSelectors.size() <= 1) {
1916 continue;
1917 }
1918
1919 const BasicSelector &sel = selector.basicSelectors.at(i: selector.basicSelectors.size() - 1);
1920
1921 if (!sel.ids.isEmpty()) {
1922 StyleRule nr;
1923 nr.selectors += selector;
1924 nr.declarations = rule.declarations;
1925 nr.order = i;
1926 idIndex.insert(key: sel.ids.at(i: 0), value: nr);
1927 } else if (!sel.elementName.isEmpty()) {
1928 StyleRule nr;
1929 nr.selectors += selector;
1930 nr.declarations = rule.declarations;
1931 nr.order = i;
1932 QString name = sel.elementName;
1933 if (nameCaseSensitivity == Qt::CaseInsensitive)
1934 name = std::move(name).toLower();
1935 nameIndex.insert(key: name, value: nr);
1936 } else {
1937 universalsSelectors += selector;
1938 }
1939 }
1940 if (!universalsSelectors.isEmpty()) {
1941 StyleRule nr;
1942 nr.selectors = universalsSelectors;
1943 nr.declarations = rule.declarations;
1944 nr.order = i;
1945 universals << nr;
1946 }
1947 }
1948 styleRules = universals;
1949}

1966
1967bool StyleSelector::selectorMatches(const Selector &selector, NodePtr node)
1968{
1969 if (selector.basicSelectors.isEmpty())
1970 return false;
1971
1972 if (selector.basicSelectors.at(i: 0).relationToNext == BasicSelector::NoRelation) {
1973 if (selector.basicSelectors.size() != 1)
1974 return false;
1975 return basicSelectorMatches(rule: selector.basicSelectors.at(i: 0), node);
1976 }
1977 if (selector.basicSelectors.size() <= 1)
1978 return false;
1979
1980 int i = selector.basicSelectors.size() - 1;
1981 node = duplicateNode(node);
1982 bool match = true;
1983
1984 BasicSelector sel = selector.basicSelectors.at(i);
1985 do {
1986 match = basicSelectorMatches(rule: sel, node);
1987 if (!match) {
1988 if (i == selector.basicSelectors.size() - 1) // first element must always match!
1989 break;
1990 if (sel.relationToNext != BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfAncestor &&
1991 sel.relationToNext != BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfIndirectAdjecent)
1992 break;
1993 }
1994
1995 if (match || (sel.relationToNext != BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfAncestor &&
1996 sel.relationToNext != BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfIndirectAdjecent))
1997 --i;
1998
1999 if (i < 0)
2000 break;
2001
2002 sel = selector.basicSelectors.at(i);
2003 if (sel.relationToNext == BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfAncestor
2004 || sel.relationToNext == BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfParent) {
2005
2006 NodePtr nextParent = parentNode(node);
2007 freeNode(node);
2008 node = nextParent;
2009 } else if (sel.relationToNext == BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfDirectAdjecent
2010 || sel.relationToNext == BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfIndirectAdjecent) {
2011 NodePtr previousSibling = previousSiblingNode(node);
2012 freeNode(node);
2013 node = previousSibling;
2014 }
2015 if (isNullNode(node)) {
2016 match = false;
2017 break;
2018 }
2019 } while (i >= 0 && (match || sel.relationToNext == BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfAncestor
2020 || sel.relationToNext == BasicSelector::MatchNextSelectorIfIndirectAdjecent));
2021
2022 freeNode(node);
2023
2024 return match;
2025}
2026
2027bool StyleSelector::basicSelectorMatches(const BasicSelector &sel, NodePtr node)
2028{
2029 if (!sel.attributeSelectors.isEmpty()) {
2030 if (!hasAttributes(node))
2031 return false;
2032
2033 for (int i = 0; i < sel.attributeSelectors.size(); ++i) {
2034 const QCss::AttributeSelector &a = sel.attributeSelectors.at(i);
2035
2036 const QString attrValue = attributeValue(node, aSelector: a);
2037 if (attrValue.isNull())
2038 return false;
2039
2040 switch (a.valueMatchCriterium) {
2041 case QCss::AttributeSelector::NoMatch:
2042 break;
2043 case QCss::AttributeSelector::MatchEqual:
2044 if (attrValue != a.value)
2045 return false;
2046 break;
2047 case QCss::AttributeSelector::MatchIncludes: {
2048 const auto lst = QStringView{attrValue}.tokenize(needle: u' ');
2049 bool found = false;
2050 for (auto s : lst) {
2051 if (s == a.value) {
2052 found = true;
2053 break;
2054 }
2055 }
2056 if (!found)
2057 return false;
2058 break;
2059 }
2060 case QCss::AttributeSelector::MatchDashMatch: {
2061 const QString dashPrefix = a.value + u'-';
2062 if (attrValue != a.value && !attrValue.startsWith(s: dashPrefix))
2063 return false;
2064 break;
2065 }
2066 case QCss::AttributeSelector::MatchBeginsWith:
2067 if (!attrValue.startsWith(s: a.value))
2068 return false;
2069 break;
2070 case QCss::AttributeSelector::MatchEndsWith:
2071 if (!attrValue.endsWith(s: a.value))
2072 return false;
2073 break;
2074 case QCss::AttributeSelector::MatchContains:
2075 if (!attrValue.contains(s: a.value))
2076 return false;
2077 break;
2078 }
2079 }
2080 }
2081
2082 if (!sel.elementName.isEmpty()
2083 && !nodeNameEquals(node, nodeName: sel.elementName))
2084 return false;
2085
2086 if (!sel.ids.isEmpty()
2087 && sel.ids != nodeIds(node))
2088 return false;
2089
2090 return true;
2091}

2093void StyleSelector::matchRule(NodePtr node, const StyleRule &rule, StyleSheetOrigin origin,
2094 int depth, QMultiMap<uint, StyleRule> *weightedRules)
2095{
2096 for (int j = 0; j < rule.selectors.size(); ++j) {
2097 const Selector& selector = rule.selectors.at(i: j);
2098 if (selectorMatches(selector, node)) {
2099 uint weight = rule.order
2100 + selector.specificity() *0x100
2101 + (uint(origin) + depth)*0x100000;
2102 StyleRule newRule = rule;
2103 if (rule.selectors.size() > 1) {
2104 newRule.selectors.resize(size: 1);
2105 newRule.selectors[0] = selector;
2106 }
2107 //We might have rules with the same weight if they came from a rule with several selectors
2108 weightedRules->insert(key: weight, value: newRule);
2109 }
2110 }
2111}

2116{

2135 while (it != styleSheet.idIndex.constEnd() && it.key() == key) {

2137 ++it;
2138 }
2139 }
2140 }
2141 if (!styleSheet.nameIndex.isEmpty()) {
2142 QStringList names = nodeNames(node);
2143 for (int i = 0; i < names.size(); i++) {
2144 QString name = names.at(i);

2148 while (it != styleSheet.nameIndex.constEnd() && it.key() == name) {
2149 matchRule(node, rule: it.value(), origin: styleSheet.origin, depth: styleSheet.depth, weightedRules: &weightedRules);
2150 ++it;
2151 }
2152 }
2153 }
2154 if (!medium.isEmpty()) {

2158 matchRule(node, rule: styleSheet.mediaRules.at(i).styleRules.at(i: j), origin: styleSheet.origin,
2159 depth: styleSheet.depth, weightedRules: &weightedRules);
2160 }
2161 }
2162 }
2163 }
2164 }
2165
2166 rules.reserve(size: weightedRules.size());
2167 QMultiMap<uint, StyleRule>::const_iterator it = weightedRules.constBegin();
2168 for ( ; it != weightedRules.constEnd() ; ++it)
2169 rules += *it;

2326bool Parser::parse(StyleSheet *styleSheet, Qt::CaseSensitivity nameCaseSensitivity)
2327{
2328 if (testTokenAndEndsWith(t: ATKEYWORD_SYM, str: "charset"_L1)) {
2329 while (test(t: S) || test(t: CDO) || test(t: CDC)) {}
2330 if (!next(t: STRING)) return false;
2331 if (!next(t: SEMICOLON)) return false;
2332 }
2333
2334 while (test(t: S) || test(t: CDO) || test(t: CDC)) {}
2335
2336 while (testImport()) {
2337 ImportRule rule;
2338 if (!parseImport(importRule: &rule)) return false;
2339 styleSheet->importRules.append(t: rule);
2340 while (test(t: S) || test(t: CDO) || test(t: CDC)) {}
2341 }
2342
2343 do {
2344 if (testMedia()) {
2345 MediaRule rule;
2346 if (!parseMedia(mediaRule: &rule)) return false;
2347 styleSheet->mediaRules.append(t: rule);
2348 } else if (testPage()) {
2349 PageRule rule;
2350 if (!parsePage(pageRule: &rule)) return false;
2351 styleSheet->pageRules.append(t: rule);
2352 } else if (testRuleset()) {
2353 StyleRule rule;
2354 if (!parseRuleset(styleRule: &rule)) return false;
2355 styleSheet->styleRules.append(t: rule);
2356 } else if (test(t: ATKEYWORD_SYM)) {
2357 if (!until(target: RBRACE)) return false;
2358 } else if (hasNext()) {
2359 return false;
2360 }
2361 while (test(t: S) || test(t: CDO) || test(t: CDC)) {}
2362 } while (hasNext());
2363 styleSheet->buildIndexes(nameCaseSensitivity);
2364 return true;
2365}

2508{

2514 skipSpace();
2515 Selector sel;
2516 if (!parseNextSelector(sel: &sel)) return false;
2517 styleRule->selectors.append(t: sel);
2518 }
2519
2520 skipSpace();
2521 if (!next(t: LBRACE)) return false;
2522 const int declarationStart = index;
2523
2524 do {
2525 skipSpace();
2526 Declaration decl;
2527 const int rewind = index;
2528 if (!parseNextDeclaration(declaration: &decl)) {
2529 index = rewind;

2531 const int semicolonIndex = index;

2536 if (foundSemicolon && semicolonIndex < index) {
2537 decl = Declaration();
2538 index = semicolonIndex - 1;
2539 } else {
2540 skipSpace();
2541 return foundRBrace;
2542 }
2543 }
2544 if (!decl.isEmpty())
2545 styleRule->declarations.append(t: decl);

2570bool Parser::parseSimpleSelector(BasicSelector *basicSel)
2571{
2572 int minCount = 0;
2573 if (lookupElementName()) {
2574 if (!parseElementName(name: &basicSel->elementName)) return false;
2575 } else {
2576 prev();
2577 minCount = 1;
2578 }
2579 bool onceMore;
2580 int count = 0;
2581 do {
2582 onceMore = false;
2583 if (test(t: HASH)) {
2584 QString theid = lexem();
2585 // chop off leading #
2586 theid.remove(i: 0, len: 1);
2587 basicSel->ids.append(t: theid);
2588 onceMore = true;
2589 } else if (testClass()) {
2590 onceMore = true;
2591 AttributeSelector a;
2592 a.name = "class"_L1;
2593 a.valueMatchCriterium = AttributeSelector::MatchIncludes;
2594 if (!parseClass(name: &a.value)) return false;
2595 basicSel->attributeSelectors.append(t: a);
2596 } else if (testAttrib()) {
2597 onceMore = true;
2598 AttributeSelector a;
2599 if (!parseAttrib(attr: &a)) return false;
2600 basicSel->attributeSelectors.append(t: a);
2601 } else if (testPseudo()) {
2602 onceMore = true;
2603 Pseudo ps;
2604 if (!parsePseudo(pseudo: &ps)) return false;
2605 basicSel->pseudos.append(t: ps);
2606 }
2607 if (onceMore) ++count;
2608 } while (onceMore);
2609 return count >= minCount;

2717bool Parser::parseExpr(QList<Value> *values)
2718{
2719 Value val;
2720 if (!parseTerm(value: &val)) return false;
2721 values->append(t: val);
2722 bool onceMore;
2723 do {
2724 onceMore = false;
2725 val = Value();
2726 if (!parseNextOperator(value: &val)) return false;
2727 if (val.type != QCss::Value::Unknown)
2728 values->append(t: val);
2729 if (testTerm()) {
2730 onceMore = true;
2731 val = Value();
2732 if (!parseTerm(value: &val)) return false;
2733 values->append(t: val);
2734 }
2735 } while (onceMore);

2751bool Parser::parseTerm(Value *value)
2752{
2753 QString str = lexem();
2754 bool haveUnary = false;
2755 if (lookup() == PLUS || lookup() == MINUS) {
2756 haveUnary = true;
2757 if (!hasNext()) return false;
2758 next();
2759 str += lexem();
2760 }
2761
2762 value->variant = str;
2763 value->type = QCss::Value::String;
2764 switch (lookup()) {
2765 case NUMBER:
2766 value->type = Value::Number;
2767 value->variant.convert(type: QMetaType::fromType<double>());
2768 break;
2769 case PERCENTAGE:
2770 value->type = Value::Percentage;
2771 str.chop(n: 1); // strip off %
2772 value->variant = str;
2773 break;
2774 case LENGTH:
2775 value->type = Value::Length;
2776 break;
2777
2778 case STRING:
2779 if (haveUnary) return false;
2780 value->type = Value::String;
2781 str.chop(n: 1);
2782 str.remove(i: 0, len: 1);
2783 value->variant = str;
2784 break;
2785 case IDENT: {
2786 if (haveUnary) return false;
2787 value->type = Value::Identifier;
2788 const int theid = findKnownValue(name: str, start: values, numValues: NumKnownValues);
2789 if (theid != 0) {
2790 value->type = Value::KnownIdentifier;
2791 value->variant = theid;
2792 }
2793 break;
2794 }
2795 default: {
2796 if (haveUnary) return false;
2797 prev();
2798 if (testHexColor()) {
2799 QColor col;
2800 if (!parseHexColor(col: &col)) return false;
2801 value->type = Value::Color;
2802 value->variant = col;
2803 } else if (testFunction()) {
2804 QString name, args;
2805 if (!parseFunction(name: &name, args: &args)) return false;
2806 if (name == "url"_L1) {
2807 value->type = Value::Uri;
2808 removeOptionalQuotes(str: &args);
2809 if (QFileInfo(args).isRelative() && !sourcePath.isEmpty()) {
2810 args.prepend(s: sourcePath);
2811 }
2812 value->variant = args;
2813 } else {
2814 value->type = Value::Function;
2815 value->variant = QStringList() << name << args;
2816 }
2817 } else {
2818 return recordError();
2819 }
2820 return true;
2821 }
2822 }
2823 skipSpace();
2824 return true;
2825}

2827bool Parser::parseFunction(QString *name, QString *args)
2828{
2829 *name = lexem();
2830 name->chop(n: 1);
2831 // until(RPAREN) needs FUNCTION token at index-1 to work properly
2832 int start = index;
2833 skipSpace();
2834 std::swap(a&: start, b&: index);
2835 if (!until(target: RPAREN)) return false;
2836 for (int i = start; i < index - 1; ++i)
2837 args->append(s: symbols.at(i).lexem());
2838 /*
2839 if (!nextExpr(&arguments)) return false;
2840 if (!next(RPAREN)) return false;
2841 */
2842 skipSpace();
2843 return true;

2921bool Parser::until(QCss::TokenType target, QCss::TokenType target2)
2922{
2923 int braceCount = 0;
2924 int brackCount = 0;
2925 int parenCount = 0;
2926 if (index) {
2927 switch(symbols.at(i: index-1).token) {
2928 case LBRACE: ++braceCount; break;
2929 case LBRACKET: ++brackCount; break;
2930 case FUNCTION:
2931 case LPAREN: ++parenCount; break;
2932 default: ;
2933 }
2934 }
2935 while (index < symbols.size()) {
2936 QCss::TokenType t = symbols.at(i: index++).token;
2937 switch (t) {
2938 case LBRACE: ++braceCount; break;
2939 case RBRACE: --braceCount; break;
2940 case LBRACKET: ++brackCount; break;
2941 case RBRACKET: --brackCount; break;
2942 case FUNCTION:
2943 case LPAREN: ++parenCount; break;
2944 case RPAREN: --parenCount; break;
2945 default: break;
2946 }
2947 if ((t == target || (target2 != NONE && t == target2))
2948 && braceCount <= 0
2949 && brackCount <= 0
2950 && parenCount <= 0)
2951 return true;
2952
2953 if (braceCount < 0 || brackCount < 0 || parenCount < 0) {
2954 --index;
2955 break;
2956 }
2957 }
2958 return false;
2959}
